Company Overview of Allstate Assurance Company Separate Account B



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Allstate Assurance Company Separate Account B is an open-ended variable annuity equity mutual fund launched and managed by Provident Investment Management, LLC. The fund invests in the public equity markets of the United States. It makes its investments in the stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. The fund invests in stocks of companies operating across all market capitalization. It benchmarks the performance of its portfolio against the S&P 500 Index. The fund was previously known as Provident National Assurance Company Separate Account B. Allstate Assurance Company Separate Account B was formed on August 21, 1967 and is domiciled in the United States.


1 Fountain SquareChattanooga, TN 37402United StatesFounded in 1967



Phone: 423-294-1011

Fax: 423-294-2590








