our home, your family, your bike or your boat, see how Allstate can help protect the things that matter most to you in life.What Is Hazard Insurance?Your house is not just your home; it's likely also one of the most valuable things you own. While you have homeowners insurance to help protect you and that investment, what exactly does it cover? Homeowners policies usually help provide coverage from damage from certain hazards (or perils), such as fire, hail or vandalism. This overview of homeowners insurance is a great place to start, but it's also a good idea to you review your policy so you know your specific coverage.Learn More What Is Comprehensive Auto Insurance?When you hear the word "comprehensive," you might think "all-encompassing." But when it comes to insurance, the word has a different meaning. Simply put, comprehensive coverage helps protect you against damage to your car that is not the result of a collision - such as theft or a fallen tree branch. I'd be happy to talk to you about whether comprehensive coverage makes sense for you.Learn More Do I Need Renters Insurance in College?If you're heading off to college, you may be thinking about football games and all night study sessions. You probably aren't imagining someone taking your smartphone or your roommate's failed attempt at dinner and the resulting kitchen fire. But those are, unfortunately, possibilities whether you live on campus or are renting an apartment. Since you may be bringing some expensive items with you, like a laptop and television, consider this overview on protecting your belongings while you're away from home.Learn More Term Life Insurance 101Term life insurance can be an affordable way to help protect your loved ones for a set amount of time - typically anywhere from one to 30 years. You'll be covered for the length of the selected term, and your beneficiaries will receive the policy benefit if you should pass away during that time. If you're interested in term insurance, this brief overview is a great place to start. I know that buying life insurance can be a difficult decision, but it is an important one. That's why I’m here to help you choose the best options for you.Learn More Tips for Managing Small Business Insurance CostsBeing a small business owner can mean working long after you've "closed" for the day. The to-do list is never done, and you're frequently juggling priorities. But you may want to move reviewing your business insurance to the top of that list. There's a lot to consider when covering the business you put your heart into. From making sure you having the right amount of protection to managing risks and bundling coverages, I'm here to help you choose the coverage that is right for your business.Learn More Is a Wedding Covered by Event Insurance?Considerable investments of time and money can go into planning a wedding. Two types of event insurance may be available to help protect that investment.Learn More Comparing Motorcycle Insurance QuotesWhether you're about to buy your first bike or you've been riding for years, you know there's nothing quite like being out on a motorcycle. From weekend tours to a fun way to commute, it's an important part of your life — one you know you need to help protect with motorcycle insurance. Before you start shopping for motorcycle coverage, here are a few steps to follow that may help you choose the policy that best fits your needs.Learn More Do I Need ATV Insurance?The coverages that come with an all-terrain vehicle policy may help protect you and your ATV in key ways. Most policies include coverage for the ATV that may help pay for repairs after a crash or other unexpected event, like theft or fire. In addition, liability protection may help prevent you from paying out of pocket if you accidentally injure someone else or damage their property. In some cases, you may even be legally required to carry ATV insurance. Give me a call for more information about what types of protections ATV insurance may provide and what may be required in our neck of the woods.Learn More Condo InsuranceYou found the perfect condominium, called about the utilities and have movers lined up. But before you move in, do you have the right coverage for your new home? Condos are unique in the way they are insured - both you and the condo association need policies. From common areas to personal property, it's important that you understand what your policy covers and what your condo association's insurance may help protect. Take a look at this overview of condominium insurance, and then let's make sure you have the coverage you need.Learn More Have Policy Questions? I Can Help!Whether you're moving, test driving a car or considering buying life insurance, an agent's expertise may come in handy. Certain life events and policy questions are best addressed with an insurance agent consultation.Learn More What's Umbrella Insurance?You have insurance to help protect your home and car, but what happens in situations where your standard insurance coverage is not enough? That's when a personal umbrella insurance policy (PUP) could help. If you're found legally responsible for damages resulting from an accident or if you're sued, a PUP may help prevent you from paying out of pocket for costs that exceed the limits of your homeowners or auto insurance. A PUP from Allstate may help cover attorney costs and lost wages, even if you're out of the country. If you're interested in increasing your protection, I'd be happy to talk to you about umbrella coverage today.Learn More Show moreShow lessInsurance Products & ServicesInsurance is unlike any other product out there - you pay for it and hope you never have to use it. And that makes paying more than you need to that much more uncomfortable.With a policy from Allstate, you can help keep your insurance costs low with the wide variety of discounts we offer. Keep in mind, not all discounts are available in every state. The best way to get all that you qualify for is to get an insurance quote specific to Colorado Springs.You can get a rough "ballpark" insurance quote from many companies online, but talking with an agent allows you to ask questions and get a quote for coverage that matters most to you. As an Allstate agent, I can prepare a quote that details the coverage, deductibles (your portion of a loss) and cost (premium) of your insurance policy.Insurance products and services offered at my Allstate agency include:Auto InsuranceCar InsuranceFlood InsuranceInsuranceLife InsuranceMotorcycle InsuranceHome InsuranceInsurance QuoteInsurance AgencyBusiness InsuranceAnnuitiesRetirementCollege Savings PlanContactPhone(719) 574-9922(719) 574-9922Email:rkiedinger@allstate.comrkiedinger@allstate.comAddress:7615 Astn Blfs Pkwy, Unit 200Colorado Springs, CO 80920Get DirectionsLandmarks:Woodmen Rd and Austin BluffsAreas Served:Proud to serve the areas of Colorado Springs, Monument, Black Forest, Peyton, Falcon, Calhan, Elbert. Call or email me today for a personalized insurance review.Office Hours:Mon9:00 AM - 5:00 PMTue9:00 AM - 6:00 PMWed9:00 AM - 6:00 PMThu9:00 AM - 6:00 PMFri9:00 AM - 5:00 PMSatBy AppointmentSunClosedAvailable By Appointment: SaturdayAfter-Hours Appointments AvailableAvailable 24/7 at (719) 574-9922Available 24/7 at (719) 574-9922You can view my financial industry experience and background at FINRA’s BrokerCheckOther Locations:My AccountLog inPrint ID cardView claimsPay billHere to Help YouHonoring First RespondersThe Kiedinger Agency showed its appreciation for local law enforcement officials and first responders by hosting a bagels and coffee breakfast event at our Colorado Springs office. It was great meeting these professionals who protect and serve our local community. Share This Location
