What's the Difference Between Term and Permanent Life Insurance?Why It Pays to Build Your Retirement Account NowPlan Your Financial Future.Buy vs. Lease CalculatorBe Ready For Whatever the Road May Bring.Life insurance policies typically fall into two categories: term or permanent insurance. Which type of policy is right for you?See how much you need to save to help reach your retirement goal—and what it could cost if you put off saving.New Family? Nearing Retirement? Make sure you're doing all you can to protect the life you deserve—no matter what stage you're at in life.What’s more cost efficient – buying or leasing a car? This calculator can help crunch the numbers.From fixing flats to getting a jump, Allstate’s roadside assistance products can help get you back on the road.Learn moreLearn moreLearn moreLearn moreLearn more     Protect What Matters MostWhether it's your home, your family, your bike or your boat, see how Allstate can help protect the things that matter most to you in life.What Is Hazard Insurance?Your house is not just your home; it's likely also one of the most valuable things you own. While you have homeowners insurance to help protect you and that investment, what exactly does it cover? Homeowners policies usually help provide coverage from damage from certain hazards (or perils), such as fire, hail or vandalism. This overview of homeowners insurance is a great place to start, but it's also a good idea to you review your policy so you know your specific coverage.Learn More What Is Comprehensive Auto Insurance?When you hear the word "comprehensive," you might think "all-encompassing." But when it comes to insurance, the word has a different meaning. Simply put, comprehensive coverage helps protect you against damage to your car that is not the result of a collision - such as theft or a fallen tree branch. I'd be happy to talk to you about whether comprehensive coverage makes sense for you.Learn More Do I Need Renters Insurance in College?If you're heading off to college, you may be thinking about football games and all night study sessions. You probably aren't imagining someone taking your smartphone or your roommate's failed attempt at dinner and the resulting kitchen fire. But those are, unfortunately, possibilities whether you live on campus or are renting an apartment. Since you may be bringing some expensive items with you, like a laptop and television, consider this overview on protecting your belongings while you're away from home.Learn More Term Life Insurance 101Term life insurance can be an affordable way to help protect your loved ones for a set amount of time - typically anywhere from one to 30 years. You'll be covered for the length of the selected term, and your beneficiaries will receive the policy benefit if you should pass away during that time. If you're interested in term insurance, this brief overview is a great place to start. I know that buying life insurance can be a difficult decision, but it is an important one. That's why I’m here to help you choose the best options for you.Learn More Tips for Managing Small Business Insurance CostsBeing a small business owner can mean working long after you've "closed" for the day. The to-do list is never done, and you're frequently juggling priorities. But you may want to move reviewing your business insurance to the top of that list. There's a lot to consider when covering the business you put your heart into. From making sure you having the right amount of protection to managing risks and bundling coverages, I'm here to help you choose the coverage that is right for your business.Learn More Is a Wedding Covered by Event Insurance?Considerable investments of time and money can go into planning a wedding. Two types of event insurance may be available to help protect that investment.Learn More Comparing Motorcycle Insurance QuotesWhether you're about to buy your first bike or you've been riding for years, you know there's nothing quite like being out on a motorcycle. From weekend tours to a fun way to commute, it's an important part of your life — one you know you need to help protect with motorcycle insurance. Before you start shopping for motorcycle coverage, here are a few steps to follow that may help you choose the policy that best fits your needs.Learn More Do I Need ATV Insurance?The coverages that come with an all-terrain vehicle policy may help protect you and your ATV in key ways. Most policies include coverage for the ATV that may help pay for repairs after a crash or other unexpected event, like theft or fire. In addition, liability protection may help prevent you from paying out of pocket if you accidentally injure someone else or damage their property. In some cases, you may even be legally required to carry ATV insurance. Give me a call for more information about what types of protections ATV insurance may provide and what may be required in our neck of the woods.Learn More Condo InsuranceYou found the perfect condominium, called about the utilities and have movers lined up. But before you move in, do you have the right coverage for your new home? Condos are unique in the way they are insured - both you and the condo association need policies. From common areas to personal property, it's important that you understand what your policy covers and what your condo association's insurance may help protect. Take a look at this overview of condominium insurance, and then let's make sure you have the coverage you need.Learn More Have Policy Questions? I Can Help!Whether you're moving, test driving a car or considering buying life insurance, an agent's expertise may come in handy. Certain life events and policy questions are best addressed with an insurance agent consultation.Learn More What's Umbrella Insurance?You have insurance to help protect your home and car, but what happens in situations where your standard insurance coverage is not enough? That's when a personal umbrella insurance policy (PUP) could help. If you're found legally responsible for damages resulting from an accident or if you're sued, a PUP may help prevent you from paying out of pocket for costs that exceed the limits of your homeowners or auto insurance. A PUP from Allstate may help cover attorney costs and lost wages, even if you're out of the country. If you're interested in increasing your protection, I'd be happy to talk to you about umbrella coverage today.Learn More Richard Kiedinger is insurance licensed in the state(s) of Colorado. If you do not reside in the state(s) of Colorado, please go to the Find an Agent section on allstate.com to search for another Allstate Agent or Personal Financial Representative. Subject to terms, conditions & availability. This material is intended for educational purposes only. Auto and homeowners insurance, and other property and casualty insurance products, are available from Allstate Insurance Company, Allstate Indemnity Company, Allstate Property and Casualty Insurance Company and Allstate Fire and Casualty Insurance Company (Home Offices: Northbrook, IL); Allstate New Jersey Insurance Company and Allstate New Jersey Property and Casualty Insurance Company (Home Offices: Bridgewater, NJ); and Allstate County Mutual Insurance Company and Allstate Texas Lloyd's (Home Offices: Irving, TX). Life insurance issued by Allstate Life Insurance Company: Northbrook, IL; and American Heritage Life Insurance Company: Jacksonville, FL. In New York, Allstate Life Insurance Company of New York: Hauppauge, NY. Securities offered by Personal Financial Representatives through Allstate Financial Services, LLC (LSA Securities in LA and PA). Registered Broker-Dealer. Member FINRA, SIPC. Main Office: 2920 South 84th Street, Lincoln, NE 68506. (877) 525-5727.Check the background of this firm on FINRA's BrokerCheck website.CompanyOur StoryAllstate OverviewAllstate FoundationCorporate ResponsibilityInvestorsNewsroomCareersMayhemQuick LinksContact UsAuto InsuranceHome Insu